Gene's right, RHCOS is still affected. The kernel argument approach is the correct mitigation — it blacklists the vulnerable af_alg AEAD init function at boot so the module never loads.

One thing to change — the Ignition version should be 3.5.0 to match our existing MachineConfigs, not 3.4.0. Using a different version can cause RenderDegraded on the MCP.

Nothing on the cluster uses AF_ALG AEAD sockets so there's no functional impact from disabling it.

This will trigger a rolling reboot across all nodes. I'd recommend we apply it during or right after the Nexus maintenance window on April 11 so we don't take two separate rolling reboots.